        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tls): add subjectAltName to auto-generated gateway self-signed certificate (fixes #96910)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96910.\n\nWhen gateway TLS is enabled with `autoGenerate=true` (the default), the self-signed certificate is generated with only `CN=openclaw-gateway` and no `subjectAltName` extension. Node.js ≥17 ignores the CN for hostname/IP verification per RFC 6125, so the CLI probe to `wss://127.0.0.1:18789` fails.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- New certs: added `-addext subjectAltName=...` to the openssl command\n- Existing certs: auto-detect CN-only certs and regenerate with SANs\n- Regeneration is **transactional**: old files renamed to `.bak`, restored on failure\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `src/infra/tls/gateway.ts`: Added SAN extension, CN-only detection, transactional upgrade with backup/rollback\n- `src/infra/tls/gateway.test.ts`: Added regression tests for upgrade and fresh generation\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/tls/gateway.test.ts` — 9/9 passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**New cert:**\n```\n$ openssl x509 -in gateway-cert.pem -noout -ext subjectAltName\nX509v3 Subject Alternative Name:\n    DNS:localhost, DNS:<hostname>, IP Address:127.0.0.1, IP Address:0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1\n\n$ tls.checkServerIdentity('127.0.0.1', cert)\n✅ PASSED for 127.0.0.1\n```\n\n**Upgrade path (existing CN-only cert):**\n```\n[warn] gateway tls: upgrading CN-only certificate to include subjectAltName\n[info] gateway tls: generated self-signed cert at ...\n\nBEFORE: CN=openclaw-gateway, no SAN\nAFTER:  CN=openclaw-gateway, SAN=DNS:localhost,...,IP:127.0.0.1\n```\n\n**Transactional safety:**\n```\nOld cert → renamed to .bak\nNew cert generated\n  Success → .bak removed\n  Failure → .bak restored, original cert preserved\n```\n\n- [x] AI-assisted",
        "branch": "fix/issue-96910-gateway-tls-san-v2",
